   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>LESSON SIXTEEN THE HUMAN SPIRIT Scripture Reading: Gen 2:7; Prov 20:27; Zech 12:1b; Rom 9:1; John 4:24; Rom 1:9; Luke 1:47; Rom 8:16; Ezek.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>36:26m; 2 Tim 4:22a; John 3:6b; 1 Cor 6:17; Eph 2:22b; Gal 5:16, 25b; Rom 8:4b; Rev 1:10a OUTLINE Its creation: By Jehovah God breathing the breath of life into man Gen 2:7.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>The breath of life becoming man's spirit Prov 20:27.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Its importance ranked with the heavens and the earth Zech 12:1b.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Its three parts: The conscience Rom 9:1, compared with Rom 8:16; 1 Cor 5:3; Psa 51:10; 34:18; Deut 2:30.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Fellowship John 4:24; Rom 1:9; 7:6; Eph 6:18; Luke 1:47; Rom 8:16; 1 Cor 6:17.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Intuition 1 Cor 2:11; Mark 2:8; 8:12; John 11:33.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Its function: To contact God John 4:24.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>To receive God Ezek.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>36:26.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>To contain God 2 Tim 4:22a.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Being deadened Eph 2:1, 5a.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>Being regenerated John 3:6b: By God the Spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>With God's life John 1:13b.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>To be one spirit with the Lord 1 Cor 6:17; Rom 8:16.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>To be the dwelling place of God Eph 2:22b.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>Walking by it and according to it Gal 5:16, 25b; Rom 8:4b; Rev 1:10a.</S>
   </TEXT>
